Dr. JonN Summam, a younger son of Sir Oliver Sinclair of Rosslyu, was educated at St. Andrews‚ and obtained the Deanery of Restalrig sub- sequently to his appointment as an ordinary Lord of Session on the Spiritual side, 27 th April 1540. On this occasion he took his seat on the bench as Rector of Snaw3 and he appears as such in the Minutes of the Court until May 1542, after which there is a blank in the Register. It is probable, therefore, that Gibson was dead before 1545, Sinclair having been ap- pointed Dean, and Mr. John Spittall succeeding him as Rector of Snaw.‘·' In the Privy Seal Register is the following notice :—
